<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880928-0103 </DOCNO><HL> Raytheon Receives $409.2 Million Award For Navy Equipment </HL><SO> </SO><CO> RTN GE MD HON ROK HSC LOR LK GM GMH UTX GD NOC CTC </CO><IN> ARO </IN><G> DEF </G><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Raytheon Co. got $409.2 million in Navy contracts for submarine-control equipment and shipboard radios.    General Electric Co. was given $113.4 million in Air Force and Army contracts for radar systems, aircraft eqiupment and computer equipment.    McDonnell Douglas Corp. was issued $104.6 million in Army and Air Force contracts for helicopter equipment and aircraft test equipment.    Honeywell Inc. got $89.4 million in Army contracts for ammunition.    Rockwell International Corp. was awarded a $41.5 million Air Force contract for Minuteman missile parts.    The BMY division of Harsco Corp. got a $39.9 million Army contract for five-ton trucks.    Loral Corp. was given $38.9 million in Air Force contracts for aircraft fuel equipment and airborne radar sets.    Lockheed Corp. won $29.7 million in Air Force contracts for aircraft parts and bomb casings.    Hughes Aircraft Co., a unit of General Motors Corp., was issued a $23.1 million Navy contract for target systems.    Contel Corp.'s Federal Systems group received a $19.2 million Air Force contract for base communications systems and satellite support.    General Dynamics Corp. received $16.8 million in Navy and Air Force contracts for shipboard weapons and F-16 aircraft technical orders. -   Northrop Corp. won a $15.5 million Navy contract for radar jammers.    United Technologies Corp.'s Pratt andamp; Whitney division received a $10 million Navy contract for engine parts. </TEXT></DOC>